---
// Visual six-bucket explainer using G / R¹ / R² / E / A / T
---

<hr class="section-rule" aria-hidden="true" />

<section aria-labelledby="buckets-title">
  <div class="section-header">
    <span class="section-number">01 /</span>
    <h2 id="buckets-title" class="section-title">Six persistent buckets</h2>
  </div>

  <div class="bucket-grid">
    <div class="bucket-card" data-bucket="goals">
      <span class="bucket-letter">G</span>
      <span class="bucket-name">Goals</span>
      <p class="bucket-desc">Define what success looks like. Objectives are revisable, not set in stone — they evolve as analysis feeds back.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bucket-card" data-bucket="research">
      <span class="bucket-letter">R¹</span>
      <span class="bucket-name">Research</span>
      <p class="bucket-desc">Gather what you need to know. When execution hits a blocker, research re-engages to unblock it.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bucket-card" data-bucket="roadmap">
      <span class="bucket-letter">R²</span>
      <span class="bucket-name">Roadmap</span>
      <p class="bucket-desc">Sequence the work. When scope drifts, the roadmap adjusts — never mid-sprint.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bucket-card" data-bucket="execution">
      <span class="bucket-letter">E</span>
      <span class="bucket-name">Execution</span>
      <p class="bucket-desc">The doing. Every active project has exactly one primary next action and an explicit owner.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bucket-card" data-bucket="analysis">
      <span class="bucket-letter">A</span>
      <span class="bucket-name">Analysis</span>
      <p class="bucket-desc">Review outcomes. Analysis feeds back into Goals, Research, and Roadmap — the engine of the cycle.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bucket-card" data-bucket="time">
      <span class="bucket-letter">T</span>
      <span class="bucket-name">Time</span>
      <p class="bucket-desc">Track estimates vs actuals. When estimates mismatch, execution feeds back to recalibrate.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
